1
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:37,080
Yongnian

2
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:39,560
Xiu Mei

3
00:02:41,440 --> 00:02:42,240
Take care

4
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:02,720
Xiu Mei

5
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:05,600
Lao Kezi is gone

6
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:06,960
Where did he go?

7
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:07,840
I don't know

8
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:09,320
I just went to call him for dinner

9
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:11,280
I looked, and no one was in the room

10
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:12,400
Then I looked again

11
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:15,400
All his things have been packed up

12
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:17,120
He must have left

13
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:18,400
What do we do?

14
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:19,600
Let's go find him, quick

15
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:20,520
Okay, okay, okay

16
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:27,280
That Lao Kezi...

17
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:43,640
Slow down.

18
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:59,520
Uncle Wang, has Uncle Lao Kezi been here?

19
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:01,400
No, he hasn't.

20
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:03,440
Did Uncle Lao Kezi come for noodles today?

21
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:05,000
He didn't come today.

22
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:05,800
He didn't come.

23
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:16,680
No.

24
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:22,360
Yongnian.

25
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:25,120
Didn't Senior Brother tell you

26
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:27,000
he wanted to go back home?

27
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:28,960
Yes, he did.

28
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:31,440
Then... could it be...

29
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,440
That, that bus is...

30
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:37,080
That's the bus to his hometown.

31
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:37,840
Yes, yes, yes.

32
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:38,840
Watch out! Watch out!

33
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:40,000
Watch it!

34
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:43,600
Do you have a death wish?

35
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:47,840
Sorry about that.

36
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:01,280
Honestly, you...

37
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:02,680
Risking your life just to look for someone?

38
00:05:06,320 --> 00:05:07,560
Dad, Mom.

39
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,440
Xuan Yan.

40
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:09,480
How is it?

41
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:10,160
Any luck?

42
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:11,360
Have you heard anything?

43
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:12,240
No.

44
00:05:15,520 --> 00:05:16,360
Any news?

45
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:18,320
Dad, what's wrong?

46
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:18,720
Yongnian.

47
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:19,200
Yongnian.

48
00:05:19,280 --> 00:05:20,120
Mom, how about this,

49
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:21,280
you take Dad home first.

50
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:22,080
I'll get you a car.

51
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:24,840
Don't bother with the car.

52
00:05:24,880 --> 00:05:25,880
Go find him.

53
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:26,320
Right.

54
00:05:26,320 --> 00:05:27,400
I, I, I...

55
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:28,440
I'll go look, I'll go look.

56
00:05:28,440 --> 00:05:29,280
Let me tell you,

57
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:33,120
your Uncle Lao Kezi told me

58
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:37,120
he wanted to go to the nursing home in his town.

59
00:05:38,760 --> 00:05:39,960
Nursing home.

60
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:42,720
Xuan Yan, hurry and go check.

61
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:43,880
Okay, okay, okay.

62
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:45,120
Then, then I'll go.

63
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:46,080
You two hurry home.

64
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:47,440
You must bring Uncle back.

65
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:48,320
Don't worry.

66
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:53,680
Zhou Hongshan, oh, Zhou Hongshan...

67
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:57,000
If anything happens to him,

68
00:05:57,880 --> 00:06:00,120
that would be the greatest sin

69
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:01,760
I, Xuan Yongnian, have ever committed.

70
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:05,560
Before my parents passed, they told me

71
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:08,280
never to neglect Zhou Hongshan.

72
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:11,760
Lao Kezi counts as one of us Xuans.

73
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:13,760
He's our kin.

74
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:15,120
Old Xuan.

75
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:17,080
We're already looking, aren't we?

76
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:54,680
What's your business?

77
00:06:55,440 --> 00:06:56,680
I'm here to see someone.

78
00:06:57,200 --> 00:06:58,200
Come register first.

79
00:06:58,320 --> 00:06:59,040
Okay.

80
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:02,600
Come on in, this way.

81
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:03,320
Thank you.

82
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:27,200
Hello, hello.

83
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:28,600
I'd like to ask something.

84
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:29,520
In the past couple of days,

85
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:30,840
has any elderly man checked in here?

86
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:32,320
No.

87
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:33,400
No one.

88
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:35,000
Could you think carefully again?

89
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:36,440
His name is Zhou Hongshan.

90
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:38,480
"Hong" as in blessings, "shan" as in kind.

91
00:07:38,640 --> 00:07:39,680
Zhou Hongshan.

92
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:40,800
Are you sure it was in the past few days?

93
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:42,000
Yes, yes, just these past days.

94
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:43,120
Then no, we haven't.

95
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:43,800
If there were,

96
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:45,520
they'd all register with me.

97
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:46,680
Could you check again?

98
00:07:48,640 --> 00:07:50,240
Why don't you try the old wing?

99
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,720
I don't handle registration there.

100
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:53,000
This is the new wing.

101
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,200
Those who can't afford much,

102
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:55,760
or whose families don't really care,

103
00:07:55,760 --> 00:07:56,560
are all over there.

104
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:57,480
Go ask over there.

105
00:07:58,280 --> 00:07:59,120
Okay, thank you.

106
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:00,080
Sorry to bother you.

107
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:16,480
Grandpa

108
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:18,320
Could you take a look

109
00:08:19,080 --> 00:08:20,240
Have you seen this person?

110
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:21,400
Keep going that way

111
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:23,800
He's, he's up ahead

112
00:08:24,840 --> 00:08:25,520
What's your name?

113
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,000
What do you do?

114
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:29,720
Say something

115
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:31,200
Nobody wants them

116
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:32,880
That's why they ended up in this godforsaken place

117
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:34,679
Say something

118
00:08:35,559 --> 00:08:36,760
Ignoring me, huh?

119
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:39,039
Speak up

120
00:08:45,880 --> 00:08:46,680
Have some candy

121
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:49,800
White Rabbit candy

122
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:53,080
Uncle

123
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:55,600
Xuan Yan

124
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:56,400
Uncle

125
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:58,400
Why are you here?

126
00:08:58,480 --> 00:08:59,480
It was my fault

127
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:00,480
I'm the one who let you down

128
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:02,400
Don't say that. It has nothing to do with you

129
00:09:03,280 --> 00:09:04,680
Come on, let's talk inside

130
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:05,080
Have some candy

131
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:05,800
Come back with me

132
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:07,560
Candy, White Rabbit

133
00:09:11,560 --> 00:09:12,320
Have a seat

134
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:17,480
This whole thing

135
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:20,680
has nothing to do with you

136
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:22,320
Uncle

137
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:25,400
My dad was right

138
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:29,000
I didn't understand everyone's struggles

139
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:31,160
I didn't think it through

140
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:35,440
I watched you grow up in my arms

141
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:38,880
Don't I know what kind of person you are?

142
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:41,240
You're a good kid

143
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:45,280
Uncle

144
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:48,520
Everyone's been so worried about you

145
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:50,280
How could you

146
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:51,680
just come here without saying a word?

147
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,000
Xuan Yan

148
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:55,080
I have nowhere

149
00:09:55,640 --> 00:09:57,760
I really have nowhere else to go

150
00:09:58,760 --> 00:09:59,560
Uncle

151
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:01,600
Our home is in Peach Blossom Town

152
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:03,800
We have a home

153
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:08,680
Your dad and mom aren't young anymore

154
00:10:09,760 --> 00:10:12,160
I don't want to be a burden to the Xuan family anymore

155
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:13,400
No

156
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:14,760
Just let me stay here

157
00:10:14,760 --> 00:10:17,080
I've already arranged it with the people in charge here

158
00:10:17,160 --> 00:10:18,400
When I die

159
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:21,360
they'll give you a call

160
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:31,000
What are you doing? Get up

161
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,280
Uncle, ever since I was little

162
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:33,760
you've been at our home

163
00:10:33,760 --> 00:10:35,720
working with my dad at the factory

164
00:10:36,040 --> 00:10:37,160
and playing with me too

165
00:10:38,160 --> 00:10:39,280
In my heart

166
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:41,200
you're even closer to me than my dad

167
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:43,520
From now on

168
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:44,800
you're my Papa

169
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:48,200
I'll care for you in your old age

170
00:10:48,680 --> 00:10:49,880
and perform your last rites

171
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:51,680
Please just come home with me

172
00:10:51,680 --> 00:10:52,480
Okay?

173
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:54,800
How did our Xuan family end up like this?

174
00:10:56,760 --> 00:10:58,600
How did it come to this?

175
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:01,400
Papa, Papa

176
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:03,800
The Xuan family will get better

177
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:05,760
I promise you

178
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:09,000
I'll make sure you see it with your own eyes

179
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,120
The Xuan family thriving again

180
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:13,280
I believe you

181
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:15,640
You have what it takes

182
00:11:15,640 --> 00:11:16,440
Come on, get up

183
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:18,880
Get up

184
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:27,880
Alright then, let's go home

185
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:42,800
It's almost four o'clock

186
00:12:02,920 --> 00:12:03,720
Papa

187
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:11,440
Dad, Mom

188
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,000
Uncle's back

189
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:23,480
You...

190
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:26,400
Senior Brother, oh Senior Brother

191
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:27,240
Yongnian

192
00:12:29,760 --> 00:12:31,520
Don't run off again next time

193
00:12:31,760 --> 00:12:33,200
If you leave again, you know...

194
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:35,600
it'd stab me right through the heart

195
00:12:36,880 --> 00:12:37,880
All right, all right

196
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:39,400
Come on, come on

197
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:41,040
Let's go inside

198
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,400
Dad, where's Mom?

199
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:46,360
Your mom went out to the street to meet you

200
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:47,360
I forgot

201
00:12:47,360 --> 00:12:48,000
Hurry

202
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:48,640
Okay

203
00:12:49,520 --> 00:12:50,760
Come on, come on

204
00:13:05,520 --> 00:13:06,160
Mom

205
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:08,280
Uncle's back

206
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:09,880
Yes

207
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:11,840
He's home

208
00:13:12,040 --> 00:13:13,880
My dear old brother

209
00:13:15,280 --> 00:13:16,280
Didn't you say

210
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:19,480
you were just sitting around with nothing to do?

211
00:13:21,280 --> 00:13:22,960
Starting tomorrow

212
00:13:24,560 --> 00:13:26,120
the two of us will join forces

213
00:13:26,640 --> 00:13:27,920
and we'll make paper

214
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:33,520
We'll make a paper like none before

215
00:13:33,920 --> 00:13:35,880
the finest paper anyone could dream of

216
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:40,120
We'll show everyone

217
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:41,960
that the thousand-year Xuan family hasn't died out

218
00:13:43,520 --> 00:13:45,480
It's still making fine paper

219
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:47,880
Make one great sheet of paper

220
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:52,640
That's the spirit

221
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:53,640
Yes, yes, yes

222
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:54,600
That's it

223
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:55,880
Don't be sad, don't be sad

224
00:13:55,880 --> 00:13:58,480
I'm just happy you're back

225
00:13:59,280 --> 00:14:00,880
I really let you down

226
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:04,480
I'm the one who wronged you

227
00:14:06,560 --> 00:14:07,400
Next time

228
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:11,320
please don't do something like this again

229
00:14:12,080 --> 00:14:13,880
No, I won't ever leave again

230
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:17,880
It would be the death of me

231
00:14:19,480 --> 00:14:21,760
We've been together since we were twelve

232
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:23,720
For sixty years

233
00:14:25,320 --> 00:14:26,480
I'm so sorry

234
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:28,760
It's okay, you're back now

235
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:30,520
That's all that matters

236
00:14:52,640 --> 00:14:53,760
Two hundred sheets is enough.

237
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:56,520
Take a break.

238
00:14:56,560 --> 00:14:58,080
Let's do some more.

239
00:14:58,480 --> 00:14:59,600
Make a few more sheets.

240
00:15:00,560 --> 00:15:02,080
Pick the best of the best.

241
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:07,480
You can pick the best tomorrow.

242
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,160
Xiu Mei said

243
00:15:09,520 --> 00:15:11,880
two hundred sheets a day, max.

244
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:13,120
Your back can't take it.

245
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:14,640
Just sit down and rest.

246
00:15:15,480 --> 00:15:16,360
Besides,

247
00:15:16,480 --> 00:15:18,120
if we make more, I can't keep up.

248
00:15:18,560 --> 00:15:20,520
I can't even get the motions right.

249
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:25,760
Dad.

250
00:15:25,760 --> 00:15:26,360
Xuan Yan.

251
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:27,000
Papa.

252
00:15:28,280 --> 00:15:28,800
Papa.

253
00:15:29,160 --> 00:15:31,320
I brought you milk powder, sugar-free.

254
00:15:31,360 --> 00:15:32,160
It's getting cold.

255
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:33,680
Let's switch to warm cotton underwear.

256
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:35,880
The other day I saw your shoes were worn out.

257
00:15:35,920 --> 00:15:37,080
So I got you a new pair.

258
00:15:37,080 --> 00:15:38,720
Brand-name, non-slip.

259
00:15:39,640 --> 00:15:40,720
Is this all for me?

260
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:43,480
Thank you so much.

261
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:45,040
Dad,

262
00:15:45,640 --> 00:15:46,640
I brought you some medicated patches,

263
00:15:46,640 --> 00:15:48,720
and a guide to famous papers from around the world.

264
00:15:50,080 --> 00:15:51,040
Put it in the study.

265
00:15:51,040 --> 00:15:52,360
I'll be home soon.

266
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:54,640
Okay, I'll head back first then.

267
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:56,240
You two chat.

268
00:15:56,880 --> 00:15:57,640
Thanks again.

269
00:15:57,640 --> 00:15:58,400
No problem.

270
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:03,680
What a thoughtful kid.

271
00:16:06,120 --> 00:16:07,120
You old miser.

272
00:16:16,440 --> 00:16:18,280
For these out-of-town e-commerce livestreamers,

273
00:16:18,280 --> 00:16:20,120
we've set everything up for them.

274
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:21,640
Each gets a private room.

275
00:16:21,640 --> 00:16:22,760
Very nice rooms.

276
00:16:22,760 --> 00:16:24,280
The accommodations here are really quite decent.

277
00:16:24,920 --> 00:16:25,920
Here's the thing, Xiao Chen.

278
00:16:25,920 --> 00:16:27,600
A lot of times, what we think is fine

279
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:29,480
isn't necessarily what young people like today.

280
00:16:29,480 --> 00:16:30,720
Young people's tastes nowadays

281
00:16:30,720 --> 00:16:32,160
are different from ours.

282
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:33,080
So, on this,

283
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:35,360
you should listen more to the young people's opinions.

284
00:16:35,360 --> 00:16:37,280
Discuss it with them more, right?

285
00:16:37,280 --> 00:16:38,040
Xiao Lin.

286
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:39,600
Share your thoughts.

287
00:16:40,280 --> 00:16:42,520
Then I'll be so bold as to share my thoughts.

288
00:16:42,520 --> 00:16:43,920
No need to be so bold.

289
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:45,880
We're used to your straightforwardness.

290
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:46,640
Go ahead.

291
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,000
I think the hardest part

292
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:49,520
isn't actually attracting people.

293
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:51,200
The key is how to keep them.

294
00:16:51,280 --> 00:16:53,120
As long as the conditions are good enough,

295
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:55,120
young people will be willing to come here

296
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:56,600
to develop e-commerce careers.

297
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:59,040
I don't think room size matters much.

298
00:16:59,040 --> 00:17:00,880
What matters is whether we can

299
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:03,520
customize them to each person's personality and ideas.

300
00:17:03,520 --> 00:17:05,760
That way they'll feel a sense of belonging and security.

301
00:17:06,119 --> 00:17:07,359
Oh, good heavens.

302
00:17:07,359 --> 00:17:10,079
Everyone's ideas are worlds apart.

303
00:17:10,119 --> 00:17:11,119
Wanting this and that,

304
00:17:11,680 --> 00:17:12,720
it'd work me to death.

305
00:17:12,720 --> 00:17:14,520
I couldn't satisfy them all.

306
00:17:14,520 --> 00:17:16,160
Well, I think we can be more flexible.

307
00:17:16,440 --> 00:17:18,240
With oversight and a budget,

308
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:20,640
as long as the finances are transparent and compliant,

309
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:22,680
can't we give the young people more room

310
00:17:22,680 --> 00:17:23,760
to do it themselves?

311
00:17:24,359 --> 00:17:25,119
Xiao Chen.

312
00:17:25,520 --> 00:17:26,680
On these matters,

313
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:29,000
we really should listen more to the young people

314
00:17:29,040 --> 00:17:30,280
and discuss it more.

315
00:17:31,120 --> 00:17:33,800
So, I have another meeting this afternoon.

316
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:34,760
I'll leave you to it.

317
00:17:34,760 --> 00:17:35,880
You all discuss it thoroughly.

318
00:17:35,880 --> 00:17:36,200
Alright.

319
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:37,160
Thank you, Xiao Chen.

320
00:17:37,160 --> 00:17:37,640
Thank you for your hard work.

321
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:38,040
Let's go.

322
00:17:38,280 --> 00:17:39,880
Alright, goodbye, take care.

323
00:17:40,360 --> 00:17:41,600
Um, you all carry on.

324
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:42,920
I'll talk to you when I get back.

325
00:17:42,920 --> 00:17:43,640
Excuse me.

326
00:17:43,720 --> 00:17:44,400
Secretary Peng.

327
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:45,400
Secretary Peng, Secretary Peng.

328
00:17:46,480 --> 00:17:46,960
What is it?

329
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:47,640
Um,

330
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:50,520
Xin Ran can't easily refuse Xuan Yan,

331
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:52,760
but giving orders to Peach Blossom Town's businesses

332
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:54,080
will drive up costs.

333
00:17:54,280 --> 00:17:56,160
Such an unfavorable situation for Dayazhai,

334
00:17:56,280 --> 00:17:57,880
Xin Ran can't easily bring up with Zheng Guohui.

335
00:17:58,480 --> 00:17:59,680
So what she means is,

336
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:01,400
could you, representing the town,

337
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:02,520
talk to Zheng Guohui?

338
00:18:02,880 --> 00:18:05,120
Chairman Zheng might just do you the favor.

339
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:07,600
In a few days,

340
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:10,160
Dayazhai is holding its new product launch.

341
00:18:10,800 --> 00:18:12,120
Zheng Guohui will be coming over.

342
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:14,120
You'd better sort it out quickly,

343
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:15,640
figure out what else they need,

344
00:18:15,640 --> 00:18:16,760
and what problems we can proactively

345
00:18:16,760 --> 00:18:18,280
solve for them.

346
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:19,400
Understood.

347
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:20,160
Don't tell me

348
00:18:20,760 --> 00:18:22,120
when we ask someone for a favor,

349
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:23,880
we show up empty-handed?

350
00:18:23,920 --> 00:18:25,280
You don't even get that?

351
00:18:25,280 --> 00:18:25,760
Understood.

352
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:26,440
I'm off.

353
00:18:26,440 --> 00:18:27,600
I'll get on it as soon as I'm back.

354
00:18:27,600 --> 00:18:28,200
Good.

355
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:29,200
Take it easy.

356
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:29,720
Okay.

357
00:18:35,480 --> 00:18:36,160
Careful, careful

358
00:18:40,520 --> 00:18:41,760
Xiu Mei, take a look

359
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:42,960
It's beautiful

360
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:46,400
Truly gorgeous

361
00:18:48,320 --> 00:18:49,880
This paper is quite interesting

362
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:51,080
Xuan Yan

363
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:53,520
Where did he pop out from?

364
00:18:53,520 --> 00:18:54,720
This paper is intriguing

365
00:18:56,520 --> 00:18:57,440
Then tell us about it

366
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:03,760
It has the traits of Jade Tablet Paper

367
00:19:03,760 --> 00:19:05,680
and also of White Deer Paper

368
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:09,760
So you actually know your stuff?

369
00:19:10,960 --> 00:19:11,760
Dad

370
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:13,680
Don't underestimate me

371
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:15,480
Maybe I do know a thing or two

372
00:19:15,480 --> 00:19:16,520
Perhaps even more than you do

373
00:19:16,520 --> 00:19:17,200
Alright

374
00:19:17,840 --> 00:19:21,080
Jade Tablet Paper was the finest paper of the Song dynasty

375
00:19:21,320 --> 00:19:24,000
White Deer Paper first emerged in the Yuan dynasty

376
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,640
used by Taoists to inscribe talismans

377
00:19:25,680 --> 00:19:26,920
called White Talisman Paper

378
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:31,600
Later, the great calligrapher Zhao Mengfu used it

379
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:34,080
He found the name too crude

380
00:19:34,360 --> 00:19:36,000
Noticing that the paper screen

381
00:19:36,520 --> 00:19:37,760
was embroidered with deer patterns

382
00:19:38,320 --> 00:19:40,040
he renamed it White Deer Paper

383
00:19:40,840 --> 00:19:42,800
Each ream was stamped with

384
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:45,520
"For Imperial Use" and a white deer seal

385
00:19:45,520 --> 00:19:47,080
"For Imperial Use" meant reserved for emperors

386
00:19:47,080 --> 00:19:49,360
It represented the late Yuan and early Ming

387
00:19:49,480 --> 00:19:51,600
the peak of papermaking craftsmanship

388
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:54,160
The two of you combined them

389
00:19:55,080 --> 00:19:57,520
and created Jade Tablet White Deer Paper

390
00:19:58,920 --> 00:19:59,720
Look at that

391
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,000
This kid really knows more than we do

392
00:20:02,360 --> 00:20:04,000
If you asked me to explain all this in detail

393
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,960
I couldn't do it

394
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:09,240
Tell me, how's this paper?

395
00:20:09,240 --> 00:20:10,080
It's excellent

396
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:12,680
One sheet showing two distinct paper styles

397
00:20:12,680 --> 00:20:13,600
and different traits

398
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:15,360
That's choosing the best of the best

399
00:20:15,600 --> 00:20:17,400
That's true innovation

400
00:20:20,680 --> 00:20:21,920
Your dad's smiling

401
00:20:22,240 --> 00:20:23,080
That's a rare sight

402
00:20:23,520 --> 00:20:24,960
From now on, say more nice things

403
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:26,480
Your dad loves to hear them

404
00:20:27,960 --> 00:20:28,760
If I'm not mistaken

405
00:20:28,760 --> 00:20:30,760
this says "Made by Xuan Yongnian"

406
00:20:30,760 --> 00:20:31,480
That's right

407
00:20:31,720 --> 00:20:32,240
Dad

408
00:20:32,840 --> 00:20:35,000
Why did you put your own watermark on it?

409
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:35,560
Yes

410
00:20:35,560 --> 00:20:36,800
It was stamped long ago

411
00:20:36,800 --> 00:20:38,480
Didn't you make it a final edition?

412
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:40,800
Your dad later pulled me aside

413
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:42,400
and we secretly made quite a few more

414
00:20:42,480 --> 00:20:43,600
All bearing this watermark

415
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:45,320
Well, in that case

416
00:20:46,080 --> 00:20:47,400
I can sell another batch as a final edition

417
00:20:47,440 --> 00:20:48,600
Enough, enough, enough

418
00:20:48,960 --> 00:20:51,440
People bought it as a final edition

419
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:53,760
If they found out you pulled this

420
00:20:53,840 --> 00:20:55,280
they'd curse me to death

421
00:20:56,440 --> 00:20:57,440
Getting serious again

422
00:20:58,160 --> 00:20:59,240
Just a joke

423
00:20:59,560 --> 00:21:00,400
Your dad and I

424
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:03,760
wanted to craft a paper worthy of our ancestors

425
00:21:04,720 --> 00:21:07,080
We've been pondering it for days

426
00:21:07,080 --> 00:21:10,240
What truly counts as a good paper?

427
00:21:10,520 --> 00:21:11,960
Senior Brother, stop asking

428
00:21:11,960 --> 00:21:14,840
Just let Xuan Yan write you both a prescription

429
00:21:15,520 --> 00:21:16,720
The two of them, over this paper

430
00:21:16,880 --> 00:21:18,040
are about to fall ill

431
00:21:18,040 --> 00:21:20,800
That's what they call "No madness, no mastery"

432
00:21:22,320 --> 00:21:23,200
Dad, listen

433
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:25,160
Chengxintang Paper counts as good paper, right?

434
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:27,320
This Jade Tablet White Deer Paper you made

435
00:21:27,320 --> 00:21:28,360
also counts as good paper

436
00:21:28,560 --> 00:21:29,760
If you really try to rank them

437
00:21:29,760 --> 00:21:30,920
I couldn't say which is better

438
00:21:31,360 --> 00:21:32,560
If you ask me

439
00:21:32,840 --> 00:21:33,640
Go on

440
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:35,360
Why don't you do this instead

441
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:37,960
Recreate all the great papers of every dynasty

442
00:21:37,960 --> 00:21:39,600
and pass them down to future generations

443
00:21:39,760 --> 00:21:41,000
That would be far more meaningful

444
00:21:41,720 --> 00:21:43,400
Your dad wants a paper

445
00:21:43,800 --> 00:21:45,400
the very best of the best

446
00:21:45,600 --> 00:21:47,320
The best paper, you see

447
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:49,960
is one our ancestors

448
00:21:50,280 --> 00:21:52,000
never managed to create

449
00:21:52,920 --> 00:21:55,800
but our generation made it happen

450
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:57,520
That's what makes it great paper

451
00:22:01,560 --> 00:22:02,160
Son

452
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:03,760
What's up?

453
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:05,760
You've been busy lately

454
00:22:05,920 --> 00:22:07,040
So don't bother coming home for now

455
00:22:07,440 --> 00:22:09,680
I've got the two old kids at home covered

456
00:22:09,720 --> 00:22:11,360
It's fine, don't worry about us

457
00:22:11,360 --> 00:22:12,400
Okay, if I'm free

458
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:14,280
I'll come back and spend time with you

459
00:22:15,840 --> 00:22:19,040
It'd be great if you could bring Miss Lin back

460
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:21,520
Your dad would be so happy

461
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:23,280
Your dad was even asking the other day

462
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:25,920
Why hasn't that Miss Lin come by?

463
00:22:25,920 --> 00:22:28,040
I haven't seen her in ages

464
00:22:28,040 --> 00:22:29,240
I miss her

465
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:30,680
I miss her too

466
00:22:32,200 --> 00:22:34,160
She's busy, really busy

467
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:38,240
Your mom's pretty sharp, you know

468
00:22:38,840 --> 00:22:40,360
Did something happen between you two?

469
00:22:42,080 --> 00:22:43,960
What could happen? Nothing's wrong

470
00:22:44,040 --> 00:22:45,160
Well, if something did happen

471
00:22:45,160 --> 00:22:46,280
it'd definitely be your fault

472
00:22:46,280 --> 00:22:47,720
That girl is a real sweetheart

473
00:22:48,680 --> 00:22:49,360
Yes, yes, yes

474
00:22:49,360 --> 00:22:50,480
Yeah, it's my fault

475
00:22:50,480 --> 00:22:51,560
So what's the problem exactly?

476
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:53,960
No problem, I'm just joking with you

477
00:22:55,440 --> 00:22:56,320
I don't care

478
00:22:57,080 --> 00:22:59,040
No matter what it takes

479
00:22:59,080 --> 00:23:00,760
You bring that girl back here

480
00:23:01,040 --> 00:23:02,280
Okay, don't worry

481
00:23:02,360 --> 00:23:03,480
I'll definitely bring her back

482
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:05,000
If you can't bring her back

483
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:05,720
don't bother coming back either

484
00:23:05,840 --> 00:23:06,600
I'm off

485
00:23:09,840 --> 00:23:10,920
Drive safely

486
00:23:12,680 --> 00:23:13,480
Bye

487
00:23:30,920 --> 00:23:32,960
Today, we're not just talking about toys,

488
00:23:33,160 --> 00:23:35,480
but the childlike innocence

489
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:37,920
that still lives in every adult's heart.

490
00:23:38,240 --> 00:23:40,720
Who says adults can't be kids,

491
00:23:40,720 --> 00:23:41,800
or aren't little ones anymore?

492
00:23:42,200 --> 00:23:43,520
Modern adults

493
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:46,120
need more emotional comfort.

494
00:23:49,280 --> 00:23:50,680
The phenomenal debut of XuanBao,

495
00:23:50,920 --> 00:23:53,280
with its quirky, whimsical designs,

496
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:55,960
has filled a gap in the trendy toy market.

497
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:59,040
Its unique intangible heritage identity

498
00:23:59,040 --> 00:24:01,280
has also brought fresh topics

499
00:24:01,520 --> 00:24:03,240
to adult social circles.

500
00:24:03,560 --> 00:24:06,600
XuanBao is growing strong and healthy,

501
00:24:07,320 --> 00:24:10,680
showcasing itself in endless designs.

502
00:24:10,720 --> 00:24:11,680
And today,

503
00:24:11,680 --> 00:24:14,840
we're launching a brilliant new collection:

504
00:24:19,680 --> 00:24:23,600
the XuanBao Cosmic Voyage Series.

505
00:24:25,280 --> 00:24:27,800
Wonderful.

506
00:24:32,600 --> 00:24:33,360
So beautiful.

507
00:24:34,040 --> 00:24:36,080
I have every reason to believe

508
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:39,160
that as our new products keep launching,

509
00:24:39,240 --> 00:24:42,000
Dayazhai's cultural creative industry

510
00:24:42,160 --> 00:24:45,120
will reach a brand new peak.

511
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:47,200
Excellent.

512
00:24:47,600 --> 00:24:49,320
Chairman Zheng, congratulations.

513
00:24:49,520 --> 00:24:51,040
Your future is limitless.

514
00:24:51,040 --> 00:24:53,520
It's all thanks to local leaders' support.

515
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:54,960
Our pleasure, our pleasure.

516
00:24:55,600 --> 00:24:56,320
Director Lin,

517
00:24:56,320 --> 00:24:57,720
let's not stand on ceremony.

518
00:24:58,440 --> 00:25:00,480
At this launch event,

519
00:25:00,920 --> 00:25:02,880
Secretary Peng spoke with me.

520
00:25:03,440 --> 00:25:04,360
What she meant

521
00:25:04,360 --> 00:25:07,960
was to have Dayazhai's cultural products

522
00:25:07,960 --> 00:25:09,080
share a portion

523
00:25:09,240 --> 00:25:11,600
with the town's Xuan paper industry.

524
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:13,520
I can understand where she's coming from.

525
00:25:13,760 --> 00:25:16,000
But then again,

526
00:25:16,280 --> 00:25:18,400
as the saying goes, business is business.

527
00:25:18,840 --> 00:25:20,760
The market is a battlefield. It's brutal.

528
00:25:21,640 --> 00:25:23,840
If we go along with Secretary Peng's idea,

529
00:25:24,040 --> 00:25:26,680
for Dayazhai,

530
00:25:26,960 --> 00:25:28,320
the losses would be too great.

531
00:25:28,440 --> 00:25:30,920
You just said support goes both ways.

532
00:25:30,920 --> 00:25:32,240
I think that's absolutely right.

533
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:33,320
Very well said.

534
00:25:33,320 --> 00:25:34,760
A close neighbor beats a distant relative.

535
00:25:35,480 --> 00:25:36,240
Dayazhai

536
00:25:36,240 --> 00:25:37,840
develops on this land,

537
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:40,320
supporting local sister enterprises.

538
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:42,160
And the growth of those sister businesses

539
00:25:42,360 --> 00:25:44,640
will surely give back to Dayazhai.

540
00:25:45,440 --> 00:25:47,320
Together, we are a blazing fire.

541
00:25:47,800 --> 00:25:49,520
Dayazhai shifts from dominating alone

542
00:25:49,560 --> 00:25:51,960
to leading Peach Blossom Town's

543
00:25:51,960 --> 00:25:54,320
the flagship of the Xuan paper creative cluster.

544
00:25:54,920 --> 00:25:57,680
Combined with our new e-commerce base,

545
00:25:57,840 --> 00:25:59,880
we form a closed cultural creative chain,

546
00:26:00,120 --> 00:26:02,120
thereby dominating the national cultural creative market,

547
00:26:02,200 --> 00:26:05,000
seizing control of the entire industry.

548
00:26:05,440 --> 00:26:06,240
Of course,

549
00:26:06,960 --> 00:26:08,280
in the early stages,

550
00:26:08,840 --> 00:26:10,320
the costs may be a bit higher.

551
00:26:10,720 --> 00:26:13,120
But the hidden benefits are enormous.

552
00:26:13,320 --> 00:26:15,760
Dayazhai is the biggest flagship company,

553
00:26:15,760 --> 00:26:17,480
so it'll surely be the biggest beneficiary.

554
00:26:17,800 --> 00:26:18,720
You won't lose on this deal.

555
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:23,400
Look at that, just look at that.

556
00:26:23,400 --> 00:26:25,000
I really didn't expect this.

557
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:27,520
Usually, I'm the one making empty promises.

558
00:26:27,800 --> 00:26:28,600
But today,

559
00:26:28,680 --> 00:26:31,360
Director Lin made empty promises to me.

560
00:26:31,600 --> 00:26:33,760
I'm honored to pitch dreams to the Chairman.

561
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:35,400
What if they actually come true?

562
00:26:39,920 --> 00:26:40,720
President Xin,

563
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:43,800
you're the head of the Peach Blossom branch,

564
00:26:43,800 --> 00:26:44,640
the general manager.

565
00:26:45,080 --> 00:26:46,120
What's your take?

566
00:26:49,200 --> 00:26:51,200
It's fine, speak your mind.

567
00:26:51,280 --> 00:26:52,360
We're just brainstorming here.

568
00:26:54,240 --> 00:26:54,760
I...

569
00:26:57,320 --> 00:26:58,160
I think

570
00:26:58,440 --> 00:27:01,080
if things turn out as Director Lin described,

571
00:27:01,400 --> 00:27:03,080
if it can all be achieved,

572
00:27:03,960 --> 00:27:05,840
it would be wonderful.

573
00:27:08,760 --> 00:27:09,520
However,

574
00:27:11,240 --> 00:27:12,040
we still need to align it

575
00:27:12,040 --> 00:27:14,200
with Dayazhai's development strategy,

576
00:27:15,080 --> 00:27:16,080
considering the whole picture.

577
00:27:22,480 --> 00:27:23,280
President Zhang,

578
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:24,840
listen to that, just listen.

579
00:27:25,280 --> 00:27:27,440
President Xin truly lives up to being

580
00:27:27,440 --> 00:27:29,000
the head steward I picked back then.

581
00:27:29,520 --> 00:27:31,560
She sees things so pragmatically.

582
00:27:31,560 --> 00:27:33,120
That's something you should learn from.

583
00:27:43,040 --> 00:27:43,840
Yuqing.

584
00:27:43,840 --> 00:27:46,240
Why aren't you refilling Director Lin's tea?

585
00:27:46,360 --> 00:27:47,480
It's fine, no need.

586
00:27:48,240 --> 00:27:49,000
Go ahead, pour it.

587
00:27:49,080 --> 00:27:50,040
Teacher Xuan.

588
00:27:51,040 --> 00:27:54,640
Under President Xin's leadership, the Dayazhai branch

589
00:27:54,760 --> 00:27:56,520
has achieved remarkable results.

590
00:27:56,720 --> 00:27:58,920
Of course, you deserve credit too.

591
00:27:58,920 --> 00:28:00,640
Your contribution is indispensable.

592
00:28:00,920 --> 00:28:03,640
Tell me, what are your plans going forward?

593
00:28:04,520 --> 00:28:05,040
Me?

594
00:28:06,560 --> 00:28:07,760
Weren't you just discussing

595
00:28:07,760 --> 00:28:09,000
the cultural creative orders?

596
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:10,040
Haven't you finished that yet?

597
00:28:11,560 --> 00:28:12,480
Teacher Xuan.

598
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:15,800
I think I made myself very clear earlier.

599
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:18,520
Helping other Peach Blossom Town businesses

600
00:28:18,920 --> 00:28:21,200
at the expense of Dayazhai's interests?

601
00:28:22,080 --> 00:28:23,800
Isn't that a bit of a joke?

602
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:27,480
Understood.

603
00:28:28,280 --> 00:28:29,080
Chairman.

604
00:28:29,640 --> 00:28:30,800
What were you about to say?

605
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:33,760
Just now,

606
00:28:37,080 --> 00:28:38,280
what I wanted to say was,

607
00:28:39,080 --> 00:28:40,880
a person needs to know gratitude.

608
00:28:41,040 --> 00:28:43,400
Personal effort is certainly important,

609
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:46,200
but opportunity and platform

610
00:28:46,200 --> 00:28:47,480
matter more than individual effort.

611
00:28:48,040 --> 00:28:50,480
We often come across people

612
00:28:50,760 --> 00:28:52,160
whose talents go unrecognized.

613
00:28:53,880 --> 00:28:55,600
And there are plenty of them.

614
00:28:55,760 --> 00:28:58,240
You could say it's utterly commonplace.

615
00:28:58,240 --> 00:28:59,000
Why?

616
00:28:59,440 --> 00:29:02,480
Because their effort

617
00:29:03,440 --> 00:29:05,240
doesn't match up with their opportunities.

618
00:29:06,040 --> 00:29:07,800
So, in other words,

619
00:29:08,280 --> 00:29:11,680
choices sometimes matter more than effort.

620
00:29:13,520 --> 00:29:16,280
But I think it should be mutual commitment,

621
00:29:16,720 --> 00:29:17,840
lifting each other up.

622
00:29:27,680 --> 00:29:28,480
Alright.

623
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:31,480
Mutual commitment, sure.

624
00:29:32,760 --> 00:29:33,560
Director Lin.

625
00:29:33,760 --> 00:29:36,000
There's something I'd like to report to you.

626
00:29:36,640 --> 00:29:37,640
Our group company

627
00:29:37,640 --> 00:29:38,760
is currently going through

628
00:29:38,760 --> 00:29:40,440
the IPO process.

629
00:29:40,520 --> 00:29:41,240
Going forward,

630
00:29:41,240 --> 00:29:43,640
we want to focus on building

631
00:29:43,840 --> 00:29:45,240
a group of designer studios.

632
00:29:45,240 --> 00:29:45,760
President Xin.

633
00:29:46,040 --> 00:29:46,920
Did you know?

634
00:29:47,080 --> 00:29:50,400
The company will devote all its energy

635
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:53,560
to building designer teams.

636
00:29:53,560 --> 00:29:55,560
And these designer teams

637
00:29:55,560 --> 00:29:58,160
will be shaped into our group's

638
00:29:58,160 --> 00:29:59,760
core creative team.

639
00:30:00,440 --> 00:30:01,280
Finally,

640
00:30:01,280 --> 00:30:04,200
the designers on this core R&D team

641
00:30:04,280 --> 00:30:06,880
will become partners in our company.

642
00:30:06,960 --> 00:30:07,760
In the end,

643
00:30:08,920 --> 00:30:11,320
they'll hold equity in our company.

644
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:14,880
Teacher Xuan,

645
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:16,600
are you interested

646
00:30:16,680 --> 00:30:18,960
in a deep partnership with us?

647
00:30:19,760 --> 00:30:21,400
Chairman, a person like me,

648
00:30:21,880 --> 00:30:23,160
I'm used to being footloose.

649
00:30:23,200 --> 00:30:25,200
Pardon me for my life of uninhibited love of freedom.

650
00:30:25,320 --> 00:30:26,520
I'm not fit for the big stage.

651
00:30:31,760 --> 00:30:33,480
Even if you're not,

652
00:30:33,960 --> 00:30:35,400
you must have some plans, right?

653
00:30:35,480 --> 00:30:37,440
Let's not talk about tomorrow today.

654
00:30:37,600 --> 00:30:38,640
After all, tomorrow and the unexpected,

655
00:30:38,640 --> 00:30:40,480
who knows which comes first, right?

656
00:30:40,800 --> 00:30:41,760
I take it one day at a time.

657
00:30:47,560 --> 00:30:48,240
Alright.

658
00:30:48,480 --> 00:30:49,600
What time is the flight?

659
00:30:52,520 --> 00:30:53,240
It's time.

660
00:30:54,360 --> 00:30:55,280
Director Lin,

661
00:30:55,360 --> 00:30:56,120
I'm really sorry.

662
00:30:56,120 --> 00:30:58,160
Let's discuss any ideas next time.

663
00:30:59,520 --> 00:31:00,320
Chairman.

664
00:31:03,560 --> 00:31:04,360
Chairman!

665
00:31:31,600 --> 00:31:32,440
Lin Yiran

666
00:31:32,920 --> 00:31:34,520
I've been studying psychology lately

667
00:31:34,920 --> 00:31:36,000
Someone like you

668
00:31:36,080 --> 00:31:38,680
is called Avoidant Attachment Personality

669
00:31:38,960 --> 00:31:40,200
Its pathological form is

670
00:31:40,760 --> 00:31:42,600
Avoidant Personality Disorder

671
00:31:42,760 --> 00:31:44,480
Xuan Yan, tell me more details

672
00:31:45,760 --> 00:31:46,920
Cases like yours

673
00:31:47,200 --> 00:31:48,680
happen because when you were young

674
00:31:49,760 --> 00:31:50,760
you didn't receive love

675
00:31:51,040 --> 00:31:52,120
and were constantly denied

676
00:31:52,120 --> 00:31:53,440
Plus, now you're

677
00:31:53,520 --> 00:31:56,440
overly sensitive to others' opinions

678
00:31:56,560 --> 00:31:57,920
which gave you

679
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:00,240
a false belief that you don't deserve love

680
00:32:00,680 --> 00:32:02,760
That's why you habitually

681
00:32:02,760 --> 00:32:04,240
reject others' kindness toward you

682
00:32:05,560 --> 00:32:07,000
I think Xuan Yan is right

683
00:32:07,080 --> 00:32:08,480
Let him treat you

684
00:32:09,760 --> 00:32:11,440
You also self-righteously

685
00:32:11,760 --> 00:32:13,680
cut communication and suppress emotions

686
00:32:13,680 --> 00:32:14,680
thinking that this way

687
00:32:14,680 --> 00:32:17,080
you can avoid escalating conflicts

688
00:32:17,680 --> 00:32:18,880
Just like how you did to me

689
00:32:19,200 --> 00:32:20,840
using an Abrupt breakup

690
00:32:20,840 --> 00:32:22,760
to sever our feelings

691
00:32:24,520 --> 00:32:26,120
Xuan Yan, are you done yet?

692
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:31,520
Lin Yiran

693
00:32:31,840 --> 00:32:33,760
I designed a treatment plan just for you

694
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:35,760
To resolve your emotional suppression

695
00:32:36,320 --> 00:32:37,000
first

696
00:32:38,120 --> 00:32:39,440
we have to start with communication

697
00:32:40,240 --> 00:32:40,880
Right

698
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:42,680
She's suppressing her emotions right now

699
00:32:42,760 --> 00:32:44,040
She acts tough in front of you

700
00:32:44,040 --> 00:32:45,560
but misses you so much at night she can't sleep

701
00:32:45,560 --> 00:32:46,400
Taozi

702
00:32:46,520 --> 00:32:47,560
I'm not done yet

703
00:32:47,720 --> 00:32:49,680
She cries whenever she mentions you and your parents

704
00:32:49,680 --> 00:32:50,920
On the surface she seems strong

705
00:32:50,920 --> 00:32:51,760
but deep inside

706
00:32:52,360 --> 00:32:53,160
Yiran

707
00:32:55,560 --> 00:32:57,240
she's actually miserable inside

708
00:33:04,600 --> 00:33:06,680
From a craftsmanship perspective

709
00:33:06,720 --> 00:33:08,640
we habitually pursue perfection

710
00:33:09,160 --> 00:33:12,240
But in terms of artistic expression

711
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:14,200
we need to embrace some imperfections

712
00:33:14,200 --> 00:33:15,600
and find a balance between them

713
00:33:15,720 --> 00:33:16,600
Take a look

714
00:33:16,800 --> 00:33:18,840
Like this facial detail here

715
00:33:18,840 --> 00:33:21,000
It's way too smooth and flat

716
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:22,160
As perfect as I am

717
00:33:22,160 --> 00:33:23,400
that's really unnecessary

718
00:33:24,040 --> 00:33:25,520
I understand what you mean

719
00:33:25,760 --> 00:33:27,440
I'll make some adjustments

720
00:33:35,720 --> 00:33:36,520
Secretary Peng.

721
00:33:37,960 --> 00:33:38,760
Director Liao.

722
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:41,720
Secretary Peng, what did you need me for?

723
00:33:43,400 --> 00:33:44,920
Xuan Yan told Director Liao

724
00:33:44,920 --> 00:33:46,680
he's pulling out of the dragon boat race project.

725
00:33:46,680 --> 00:33:47,680
You didn't know?

726
00:33:54,520 --> 00:33:56,560
We haven't been in touch for a long time.

727
00:34:00,320 --> 00:34:02,400
Whatever happened between the two of you,

728
00:34:02,400 --> 00:34:03,520
that's your personal issue.

729
00:34:04,600 --> 00:34:06,400
But work can't be held up, right?

730
00:34:08,679 --> 00:34:11,960
The dragon head and keel in Lin Family Village are done.

731
00:34:12,639 --> 00:34:14,199
They're just waiting for Xuan Yan to inspect them.

732
00:34:15,520 --> 00:34:17,320
I asked Xuan Yan why he's quitting.

733
00:34:17,639 --> 00:34:19,920
He said he's not in the mood.

734
00:34:21,080 --> 00:34:22,679
"Not in the mood"? Is that acceptable?

735
00:34:22,960 --> 00:34:24,280
Homeland of Xuan Paper,

736
00:34:24,520 --> 00:34:26,400
The Dragon Boats Arrive.

737
00:34:27,239 --> 00:34:28,320
All my videos put together

738
00:34:28,320 --> 00:34:29,960
have racked up over 200,000 likes.

739
00:34:30,760 --> 00:34:32,199
The biggest highlight

740
00:34:32,520 --> 00:34:33,679
of our dragon boat race

741
00:34:33,679 --> 00:34:35,960
is the paper dragon boat made by Xuan Yan.

742
00:34:36,480 --> 00:34:38,000
He just says he's quitting, and that's it?

743
00:34:38,080 --> 00:34:39,520
I can't answer for this!

744
00:34:39,560 --> 00:34:40,400
Right.

745
00:34:40,719 --> 00:34:42,159
No, how can he act like this?

746
00:34:47,800 --> 00:34:50,040
You were the one who proposed this project.

747
00:34:50,040 --> 00:34:53,520
Once our Party committee approved it,

748
00:34:53,920 --> 00:34:55,960
we reported it up to the higher leadership.

749
00:34:56,040 --> 00:34:58,400
Now the city and county leaders

750
00:34:58,520 --> 00:35:00,080
are all very supportive.

751
00:35:00,320 --> 00:35:01,960
They said our idea is great,

752
00:35:02,280 --> 00:35:04,520
and told us to really make the most of it,

753
00:35:04,720 --> 00:35:07,400
to drive a huge wave of traffic

754
00:35:07,400 --> 00:35:09,000
to Peach Blossom Town's Xuan paper and tourism.

755
00:35:09,000 --> 00:35:09,800
You see,

756
00:35:10,040 --> 00:35:11,440
with Xuan Yan acting like this,

757
00:35:11,440 --> 00:35:13,160
what are we supposed to do, right?

758
00:35:19,520 --> 00:35:20,320
Director Liao,

759
00:35:20,480 --> 00:35:22,400
you're Xuan Yan's teacher, after all.

760
00:35:22,760 --> 00:35:23,960
Why don't you go talk him around?

761
00:35:24,280 --> 00:35:26,200
He doesn't even acknowledge me as his teacher anymore.

762
00:35:27,160 --> 00:35:28,520
He won't even see me.

763
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:29,520
Exactly.

764
00:35:29,520 --> 00:35:30,920
He just says he's quitting, and that's that.

765
00:35:31,040 --> 00:35:32,400
I can't answer for this.

766
00:35:32,680 --> 00:35:34,520
If there were any other way,

767
00:35:34,760 --> 00:35:36,400
I wouldn't have him doing it.

768
00:35:36,520 --> 00:35:37,960
A boat made from Xuan paper,

769
00:35:38,600 --> 00:35:40,520
only Xuan Yan knows how.

770
00:35:40,520 --> 00:35:41,200
Right.

771
00:35:42,560 --> 00:35:43,400
I mean...

772
00:35:45,520 --> 00:35:46,280
Well...

773
00:35:46,920 --> 00:35:47,680
How about this,

774
00:35:47,720 --> 00:35:48,960
let's brainstorm together again.

775
00:35:48,960 --> 00:35:50,680
I'm sure there must be another way.

776
00:35:51,680 --> 00:35:53,200
There's no time.

777
00:35:53,320 --> 00:35:55,320
Let the one who started it end it.

778
00:35:56,080 --> 00:35:56,720
Yiran,

779
00:35:56,720 --> 00:35:57,840
I think for this matter,

780
00:35:57,840 --> 00:36:00,360
you'll have to step in and smooth things over.

781
00:36:00,880 --> 00:36:02,280
He can't be this willful.

782
00:36:02,280 --> 00:36:03,560
He just quits whenever he feels like it?

783
00:36:03,640 --> 00:36:06,320
We're carrying responsibilities and burdens here.

784
00:36:08,400 --> 00:36:09,600
Secretary Peng's words

785
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:11,520
come straight from the heart.

786
00:36:11,800 --> 00:36:12,160
How about this,

787
00:36:12,160 --> 00:36:12,520
No, wait, I...

788
00:36:12,520 --> 00:36:15,640
Go back to your office and think it over carefully.

789
00:36:15,640 --> 00:36:17,000
Figure out how to handle this.

790
00:36:17,440 --> 00:36:18,120
Secretary Peng...

791
00:36:19,400 --> 00:36:20,280
Go think about it.

792
00:36:21,680 --> 00:36:22,520
Off you go.

793
00:36:40,360 --> 00:36:41,120
How was it?

794
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:43,200
We worked well together, didn't we?

795
00:36:43,600 --> 00:36:45,120
A Secretary is a Secretary, after all.

796
00:36:45,240 --> 00:36:46,480
Who hasn't been young once?

797
00:36:48,400 --> 00:36:49,560
These little romantic troubles,

798
00:36:49,560 --> 00:36:51,520
all clingy and endless.

799
00:36:51,680 --> 00:36:52,800
Right now, we've got

800
00:36:53,440 --> 00:36:55,080
so many tough battles to fight.

801
00:38:21,320 --> 00:38:22,160
You're here.

802
00:38:25,840 --> 00:38:27,360
Why did you stop making the Paper Dragon Boat?

803
00:38:29,440 --> 00:38:30,960
Why didn't you tell me you were coming?

804
00:38:31,560 --> 00:38:33,000
I would've washed my face.

805
00:38:33,320 --> 00:38:34,520
And gotten myself ready.

806
00:38:36,680 --> 00:38:38,840
I asked why you stopped making the Paper Dragon Boat.

807
00:38:39,960 --> 00:38:40,920
Not in the mood.

808
00:38:41,560 --> 00:38:42,440
Don't feel like it.

809
00:38:43,880 --> 00:38:45,560
But you already promised.

810
00:38:45,560 --> 00:38:47,680
How can you just quit on a whim?

811
00:38:48,560 --> 00:38:50,320
Well, that's just how I am.

812
00:38:50,640 --> 00:38:51,920
You know that.

813
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:56,560
Director Liao must've told you.

814
00:38:56,880 --> 00:38:58,720
Time is really tight now.

815
00:38:58,920 --> 00:39:00,320
In all his early promotion,

816
00:39:00,320 --> 00:39:01,280
he's been treating the Paper Dragon Boat

817
00:39:01,280 --> 00:39:02,760
as the biggest selling point.

818
00:39:02,760 --> 00:39:04,720
His situation's way worse than yours.

819
00:39:05,280 --> 00:39:07,560
But the problem is, I'm not in the mood.

820
00:39:07,640 --> 00:39:09,000
I don't want to do anything.

821
00:39:11,560 --> 00:39:13,000
Then what would make you do it?

822
00:39:14,360 --> 00:39:15,840
If you tell me to, I'll do it.

823
00:39:17,120 --> 00:39:18,200
Fine. Then do it.

824
00:39:18,560 --> 00:39:19,360
I'm leaving.

825
00:39:20,320 --> 00:39:21,080
Lin Yiran.

826
00:39:22,520 --> 00:39:23,520
Who are you to me?

827
00:39:23,520 --> 00:39:24,560
Ordering me around like that?

828
00:39:26,800 --> 00:39:27,520
You just said it yourself.

829
00:39:27,520 --> 00:39:28,560
If I tell you to do it, you'll do it.

830
00:39:28,640 --> 00:39:29,520
Then I'm telling you to stop this.

831
00:39:29,520 --> 00:39:30,600
Can you please stop?

832
00:39:33,040 --> 00:39:34,080
Am I making a fuss?

833
00:39:34,320 --> 00:39:35,560
You're punishing yourself.

834
00:39:36,520 --> 00:39:38,400
This whole thing wasn't your fault.

835
00:39:38,840 --> 00:39:40,440
And no one is blaming you.

836
00:39:40,880 --> 00:39:42,040
Why keep punishing yourself?

837
00:39:42,040 --> 00:39:43,360
Why won't you let yourself off the hook?

838
00:39:48,200 --> 00:39:48,920
Lin Yiran.

839
00:39:49,720 --> 00:39:50,120
Lin Yiran.

840
00:39:50,120 --> 00:39:51,600
Then what am I supposed to do?

841
00:39:52,320 --> 00:39:54,280
I nearly got your dad killed.

842
00:39:54,280 --> 00:39:55,600
You tell me what to do.

843
00:39:57,080 --> 00:39:58,200
You don't have to do anything.

844
00:39:59,560 --> 00:40:01,720
Just go back to being your old self.

845
00:40:06,080 --> 00:40:06,840
I...

846
00:40:07,040 --> 00:40:09,280
I caused your family so much trouble.

847
00:40:09,280 --> 00:40:10,960
And you want me to pretend nothing happened?

848
00:40:10,960 --> 00:40:11,640
Xuan Yan.

849
00:40:12,000 --> 00:40:14,080
Every time your parents are kind to me,

850
00:40:14,080 --> 00:40:14,960
you know how guilty I feel?

851
00:40:14,960 --> 00:40:16,000
Do you know that?

852
00:40:16,840 --> 00:40:18,520
Because of your childhood trauma,

853
00:40:19,520 --> 00:40:22,160
you've always had this sense of unworthiness.

854
00:40:23,280 --> 00:40:24,680
So you keep pushing yourself,

855
00:40:25,360 --> 00:40:26,760
to be a little better,

856
00:40:27,320 --> 00:40:28,360
and better still.

857
00:40:29,080 --> 00:40:30,760
You want, through your own effort,

858
00:40:31,320 --> 00:40:32,440
to change the past.

859
00:40:33,560 --> 00:40:35,680
You want to be strong enough to protect everyone.

860
00:40:36,320 --> 00:40:38,960
You want to prove yourself to everyone.

861
00:40:43,760 --> 00:40:45,720
No one needs you to prove anything.

862
00:40:46,840 --> 00:40:49,120
But there are people beside you who care,

863
00:40:49,760 --> 00:40:50,920
who love you.

864
00:40:53,960 --> 00:40:54,760
Lin Yiran.

865
00:41:00,920 --> 00:41:02,000
I love you so much.

866
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:05,520
And my parents love you too.

867
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:07,360
The moment my dad woke up,

868
00:41:07,440 --> 00:41:08,720
he told me he doesn't blame you.

869
00:41:08,720 --> 00:41:09,960
Neither does my mom.

870
00:41:10,320 --> 00:41:11,200
Do you know

871
00:41:11,200 --> 00:41:13,000
how much my parents miss you right now?

872
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:14,400
How much they want you to come back?

873
00:41:14,400 --> 00:41:15,680
How much they want to see you?

874
00:41:22,560 --> 00:41:23,800
The mess with my family,

875
00:41:24,960 --> 00:41:26,520
you must've heard about it.

876
00:41:28,760 --> 00:41:30,320
I lost the factory.

877
00:41:33,080 --> 00:41:34,560
It's so empty over there now.

878
00:41:35,480 --> 00:41:36,720
I'm too ashamed to go back.

879
00:41:38,520 --> 00:41:40,000
But I'm worried about them.

880
00:41:40,920 --> 00:41:42,160
Worried they're unhappy.

881
00:41:42,880 --> 00:41:44,320
So I have to go back.

882
00:41:46,200 --> 00:41:47,440
I'm hurting too.

883
00:41:53,560 --> 00:41:54,360
Lin Yiran.

884
00:41:55,440 --> 00:41:56,520
I need you.

885
00:41:56,880 --> 00:41:58,600
I need you to stand with me.

886
00:42:00,680 --> 00:42:02,600
Let's leave the past in the past.

887
00:42:04,080 --> 00:42:05,360
I want to see the Lin Yiran

888
00:42:07,160 --> 00:42:09,400
who's bold, who fights hard,

889
00:42:10,640 --> 00:42:12,400
and wears a smile on her face.

890
00:42:22,320 --> 00:42:23,080
It's okay.

891
00:42:27,760 --> 00:42:28,640
It's all in the past.

892
00:42:47,200 --> 00:42:47,920
All right.

893
00:42:57,000 --> 00:42:57,720
All right.
